issue.title: Dashboards in Octopus Deploy app are not updating but the data is being received into the index.
issue.body:
We installed the Octopus Deploy app on our search head, created an index for the data and we are receiving the data into the index correctly but the dashboards are not updating.  We first installed the app directly onto our search head and since the dashboards weren't updating, we also gave it a try to deploy the app via our deployment server to our 2 indexers as well but that also is not working.

Any ideas on what we can check?  We noticed some of the dashboards are using *.js files versus having the search string being available within the dashboards so we're not sure how to further troubleshoot the issue.

issue.title: Not getting data in
issue.body:
I'm new to Splunk and having trouble with trouble shooting why I can't get data into the dashboard. I installed the App and put in the API key and server name but, I'm having issues with installing the nodeJS modular input on a Redhat box. 
 Splunk 6.5.2
Would I be able to get a quick guide to getting data into the app? or where I should look to troubleshoot?

issue.title: Race condition v6.3
issue.body:
It appears that there may be a race condition with the modular input in `6.3`.
- `eventwriter` does not seem to be thread safe
- `async` code is a bit immature
